==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Satirical
<hw>Sa*tir"ic*al</hw>
<pr>(?)</pr>, }</mhw> <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L. <ets>satiricus</ets>: cf.
F. <ets>satirique</ets>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Of or pertaining to
satire; of the nature of satire; <as>as, a <ex>satiric</ex>
style</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Censorious; severe in language; sarcastic;
insulting.</def> ⟦ldquo⟧<xex>Satirical</xex> rogue.⟦rdquo⟧
<rj><au>Shak.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><syn><b>Syn.</b> -- Cutting; caustic; poignant; sarcastic; ironical;
bitter; reproachful; abusive.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p>-- <wordforms><wf>Sa*tir"ic*al*ly</wf>, <pos>adv.</pos> --
<wf>Sa*tir"ic*al*ness</wf>, <pos>n.</pos></wordforms>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Satirist</ent>⟦br⟧
